A woman has been charged with grievous harm for allegedly burning her former boyfriend with acid. Millicent Kagwira pleaded not guilty before Kibera Chief Magistrate Joyce Gandani. She allegedly committed the offence on March 10 in Riruta in Dagoreti Sub-county within Nairobi County. She assaulted Antony Gitonga, her former boyfriend. Police said the incident happened at 10pm when Gitonga was heading to his house from work. When he reached the gate, the woman, hidden behind the gate, splashed him with the acid. The accused person denied committing the offence and asked for lenient bond terms. Gandani released her on Sh200,000 bond with the surety if the same amount. She directed the case to be mentioned on July 7.